section.section:
"Local code violation" means a violation under the following provisions of the Baltimore City Code as amended from time to time or under any applicable code relating to the following provisions incorporated by Baltimore City by reference:
Nuisance control, waste control, and noise regulation titles of the Health Code of Baltimore City;
The public nuisance and neighborhood nuisance provisions under City Code Article 19, Police Ordinances;
City Code Article 23, Sanitation;
The Building, Fire, and Related Codes of Baltimore City; or
The Zoning Code of Baltimore City.
